&lt;P&gt;I'm not sure if you're referring to the raids or the single-group trials.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;As someone mentioned earlier, "trials" wouldn't necessarily make sense in every expansion because the lore doesn't always&amp;nbsp;center around an individual that poses challenges&amp;nbsp;to those who wish to prove themselves.&amp;nbsp; That said, we do&amp;nbsp;have scripted raid encounters every expansion with mechanics that aren't dissimilar to the MPG raids.&amp;nbsp; The difference between Hatchet the Torturer and the Trial of Adaptation is primarily lore. :)&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I liked &lt;EM&gt;almost&lt;/EM&gt; everything about the single-group&amp;nbsp;MPG trials.&amp;nbsp; They were challenging, hand-crafted, unique events that required careful and sometimes unusual tactics.&amp;nbsp; My problem with them was that the rewards were substantial... maybe a little too substantial.&amp;nbsp; High level spells, a permanent increase to the resistances hardcap and some incredibly good gear.&amp;nbsp; And I suspect this spike in itemization is one of the main reasons why they were so fondly remembered.&amp;nbsp; Ask yourself, and be completely honest, if the events would have been so popular if the rewards were a shade or two less powerful.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
